Azure Container Instances (ACI) provide a fast and simple way to run containers without managing infrastructure.

Users can deploy containers directly without worrying about orchestration or servers.

For example, running a batch job or short-lived process using ACI is quick and efficient.

A real-life use case is data processing tasks where containers run temporarily and shut down after completion.

Another example is testing containerized applications without setting up a full cluster.

ACI is ideal for simple, isolated workloads.
